<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/</link><description>Recent content in OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/1-health/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/1-health/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="health-check"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Health Check&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#health-check" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extensions are configured in the same &lt;code&gt;config.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file that we referenced in the installation step. Let&amp;rsquo;s edit the &lt;code&gt;config.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file and configure the extensions. Note that the &lt;strong&gt;pprof&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;zpages&lt;/strong&gt; extensions are already configured in the default &lt;code&gt;config.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file. For the purpose of this workshop, we will only be updating the &lt;strong&gt;health_check&lt;/strong&gt; extension to expose the port on all network interfaces on which we can access the health of the collector.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/2-performance/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/2-performance/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="performance-profiler"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Performance Profiler&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#performance-profiler" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector-contrib/blob/main/extension/pprofextension/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Profiler&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 extension enables the golang net/http/pprof endpoint. This is typically used by developers to collect performance profiles and investigate issues with the service. &lt;strong&gt;We will not be covering this in this workshop&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>OpenTelemetry Collector Extensions</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/3-zpages/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/1-opentelemetry-collector/2-extensions/3-zpages/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="zpages"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;zPages&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#zpages" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector/blob/main/extension/zpagesextension/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;zPages&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;svg class="link-ext" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M7 17 17 7"/&gt;&lt;path d="M9 7h8v8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
 are an in-process alternative to external exporters. When included, they collect and aggregate tracing and metrics information in the background; this data is served on web pages when requested. zPages are an extremely useful diagnostic feature to ensure the collector is running as expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="ServiceZ"&gt;ServiceZ&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="PipelineZ"&gt;PipelineZ&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--tab-2" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--panel-2" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="ExtensionZ"&gt;ExtensionZ&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-ninja-workshops-foundations-3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops-1-opentelemetry-collector-2-extensions-3-zpages-md-11-1--tab-0" data-tab-label="ServiceZ"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ServiceZ&lt;/strong&gt; gives an overview of the collector services and quick access to the pipelinez, extensionz, and featurez zPages. The page also provides build and runtime information.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>